glosses: to get on all fours, to bend over

examples.text: Önümdeki herif birden domalınca önümde çarptım ona.
examples.translation: I bumped into the bloke when he suddenly bent over in front of me.

glosses: to pay (an amount deemed much higher than the product or the service merited)

examples.text: Bok gibi kestiği saçım için berbere 450 lira domaldıktan sonra benim haller.
examples.translation: Me after having to pay ₺450 to the barber for a shitty haircut.

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish طوملمق (domalmak), from Old Anatolian Turkish طوملمق (domalmaq, “to become round”), ultimately a derivation from Proto-Turkic *top (“round object, ball”), whence top. Cognate with Kazakh томалау (tomalau) and Azerbaijani dombalmaq, Gagauz domalmaa. Akin to Turkish domalan.
